1 the state court administrator, who shall maintain and administer the registry. This
2 subsection does not apply to a licensed guardian. For purposes of this subsection, a
3 licensed guardian includes a guardian whose license has been suspended but
4 excludes a guardian whose license is revoked.
5 SECTION 3. AMENDMENT. Section 30.1-29-15 of the North Dakota Century Code is
6 amended and reenacted as follows:
7 30.1-29-15. (5-415) Death, resignation, or removal of conservator.
8 1. The court may remove a conservator for good cause, upon notice and hearing, or
9 accept the resignation of a conservator. After a conservator's death, resignation, or
10 removal, the court may appoint another conservator. A conservator so appointed
11 succeeds to the title and powers of the predecessor.
12 2. The court may order a conservator to be listed on a registry if the court removed the
13 conservator for good cause. A conservator listed on the registry is disqualified from
14 acting as a conservator in any conservatorship proceeding. The court shall send a
15 copy of the order to the state court administrator, who shall maintain and administer
16 the registry. This subsection does not apply to a licensed conservator. For purposes of
17 this subsection, a licensed conservator includes a conservator whose license has
18 been suspended but excludes a conservator whose license is revoked.
